Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery dinos; dark grey fabric with some mica inclusions; dark brownish grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Modern inscription on interior 'diosk' indicates findspot, despite the dedicatory text to Aphrodite and the joining sherd which was found in the Sanctuary of Aphrodite. The sherd joins Oxford AN1896-1908-G.122 and British Museum 1924,1201.60, which joins 1924,1201.49.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.12)
Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 65, no. 787, pl. XXI, no. 787)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.052)
